---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Projects | Nicholas Charriere">
  <h1 class="text-4xl mb-6 font-bold text-heading">Projects</h1>
  <div class="flex flex-col">
    <a href="https://getmocha.com" class="text-link hover:underline">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-medium pt-6">Mocha</h2>
    </a>
    <p class="pt-1">
      Mocha is an online AI powered app builder. It allows everyone to build web apps, no coding required.
    </p>
    <a href="https://github.com/srcbookdev/srcbook" class="text-link hover:underline">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-medium pt-6">Srcbook</h2>
    </a>
    <p class="pt-1">
      Srcbook is a TypeScript notebook. It runs locally, creates .srcmd files (markdown compatible) and has AI features.
    </p>
    <a href="https://github.com/nichochar" class="text-link hover:underline">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-medium pt-6">Open source</h2>
    </a>
    <p class="pt-1">
      I have contributed to many open source projects. I maintained pymemcache
      and snappass during my tenure at Pinterest. Axflow and Srcbook are also
      open-source products I've built in my current company.
    </p>
    <a href="https://blockchainsmokers.xyz" class="text-link hover:underline">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-medium pt-6">Blockchainsmokers</h2>
    </a>
    <p class="pt-1">
      I was curious about blockchain technology, so I built an NFT collection to
      learn more about it. Art and code were all from me.
    </p>
    <a href="https://avostories.com" class="text-link hover:underline">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-medium pt-6">Avostories</h2>
    </a>
    <p class="pt-1">
      Write for 5 minutes, every day. I built this app to help my wife and other
      writers develop a daily habit through gamification.
    </p>
    <a href="https://bytesizetheories.com" class="text-link hover:underline">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-medium pt-6">Byte Size Theories</h2>
    </a>
    <p class="pt-1">
      A blog focused on small bites of knowledge in software & startups.
    </p>
  </div>
</Layout>
